# express: Builds the web server.
# pg: Connects to PostgreSQL.
# express-validator: Checks if data sent to the server is valid.
# helmet: Adds security to prevent attacks.
# cors: Allows your frontend to talk to the backend.
# morgan: Logs every request (e.g., who visited your API).
# winston: Logs errors and events (free replacement for Sentry).
# dotenv: Stores secret settings (like database password).
# nodemon: Restarts the server during development.
# jest: Tests your code.